KernelPerceptron

Szabolcs Stremler

December 25, 2017

Initialization

set.seed(0)

N <- 100
X <- data.frame(matrix(rnorm(2 * N, mean=0, sd=1), N, 2))
X[seq(N+1,2*N),] <- matrix(rnorm(2 * N, mean=0, sd=1), N, 2)
colnames(X) <- c('x1', 'x2')

# generate classes
# let the class be -1 under the mirror of the hyperbolic cosine function
# and +1 above
X$y <- X[,2] <= -cosh(X[,1]) + 1.5
X$y[X$y == TRUE] <- -1
X$y[X$y == FALSE] <- 1

X$x2[X$y == 1] = X$x2[X$y == 1] + 0.5
# ggplot(X, aes(x = x1, y = x2, color = y)) + geom_point()

Train with polynomial kernel

kPctrPoly <- KernelPerceptron$new()
alpha <- kPctrPoly$train(X[,1:2], X[,3], kernel = polynomialKernel, kernelParam = 2)
print(alpha)
